Temperature Converter

Objective: Create a web-based temperature converter that allows users to convert temperatures between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin.

Time: 30 Minutes

Minimum Passing Requirements:

Input Field:
A text input field where users can enter a temperature value.
The input should accept numbers.
Dropdown Menu:
Two dropdown menus:
The first dropdown allows the user to select the temperature unit of the input (Celsius, Fahrenheit, or Kelvin).
The second dropdown allows the user to select the target unit for conversion (Celsius, Fahrenheit, or Kelvin).
Convert Button:
A button labeled "Convert" that triggers the conversion process when clicked.
Output Display:
A section to display the converted temperature value along with the selected target unit.
Formulae for Conversions: 

	Celsius to Fahrenheit: (°C × 9/5) + 32 = °F
Celsius to Kelvin: °C + 273.15 = K

Fahrenheit to Celsius: (°F − 32) × 5/9 = °C
Fahrenheit to Kelvin: ((°F − 32) × 5/9) + 273.15 = K

Kelvin to Celsius: K − 273.15 = °C
Kelvin to Fahrenheit: ((K − 273.15) × 9/5) + 32 = °F

Bonus Tasks: 
Try to make it a real-time conversion.
Make it responsive UI
Keep temperature history maintained until refresh.